\id FRT - The Text-Critical Greek New Testament 
\mt1 The Text-Critical Greek New Testament  
\mt2 Byzantine Text  
\ib  
\is1 Greek text compiled by  
\is2 Robert Adam Boyd  
\ib  
\is1 Introduction, Footnotes, and Appendices by  
\is2 Robert Adam Boyd  
\ib  
\im The text, introduction, footnotes, and appendices of this edition are hereby released into the Public Domain. Consequently, any prior copyright restrictions on the introduction, footnotes, and appendices of this edition are hereby revoked.  
\ib  
\im Front Cover: page 60 of the 3rd edition of Stephanus’ Greek New Testament  
\im Back Cover: page 204 of the 3rd edition of Stephanus’ Greek New Testament  
\ib  
\im Images from Stephanus’ 3rd edition of the Greek New Testament are incorporated into the front and back cover as a tribute to his work with the Byzantine Greek text and as a memorial to the fact that he was the first to publish a Greek New Testament with text-critical notes. The back cover is Stephanus’ printing emblem, which is inspired by Romans 11:17-24. The words \it noli altum sapere\it* (“do not be high minded”) are a direct quotation from Romans 11:20 in the Latin Vulgate.  
\ib  
\im Typesetting and software support by J. Jeffrey Dodson  